    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1658"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1658">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2327.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Jefferson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 35.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Upon request of the Minister of Nicaragua at
                    Washington, who had received a telegram from his Government to the effect that
                    Clifford D. Sands had led an unsuccessful attack on the barracks at Bluefields,
                    the Consul at that place was instructed by a telegram dated July 7 to report
                    regarding the matter, and replied in a telegram dated July 9 that Sands was
                    brought into the Consulate at 1 o’clock a.m., July 6, badly wounded, and was
                    delivered to the authorities and sent to a hospital on July 8.</p>
                <p>A copy of a memorandum<note n="2" xml:id="d1658fn2">Not printed.</note> from the
                    Minister of Nicaragua at Washington, in relation to the matter, is enclosed
                    herewith for your information.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/> [Not signed.]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
